 fixed entities but can undergo radical remodeling and plasticity throughout their lifetime. Memories, preferences, and rewards/punishments can persist despite changes in the substrate.</p></li><li><p>Goal-Directedness: The core of being a self is the ability to pursue goals. Selves can be nested and overlapping, cooperating and competing at different levels. Higher-level selves can deform the option space for lower-level selves, enabling them to achieve intelligent goals.</p></li><li><p>Scaling of Intelligence: Intelligence is defined as the competency of navigating any space, not just physical space. This includes morphospace, transcriptional space, physiological space, etc. Intelligence is measured by the ability to navigate to optimal regions while avoiding local minima.</p></li></ol><p>The TAME framework provides insights into the nature of cognition, the importance of plasticity and goal-directedness, and the scaling of intelligence in biological systems. It aims to provide a broader understanding of cognitive processes beyond traditional human-centric perspectives.</p></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-between lg:block"><div class="text-xs flex items-center justify-center gap-1 self-center pt-2 !invisible"><button disabled="" class="dark:text-white disabled:text-gray-300 dark:disabled:text-gray-400"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-3 w-3" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="15 18 9 12 15 6"></polyline></svg></button><span class="flex-grow flex-shrink-0">1 / 1</span><button disabled="" class="dark:text-white disabled:text-gray-300 dark:disabled:text-gray-400"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" stroke-width="1.5" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="h-3 w-3" height="1em" width="1em" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg"><polyline points="9 18 15 12 9 6"></polyline></svg></but